OT/ICS Introduction Course: Section 5

OSINT for Industrial Controls
whole course on this is on Mike's youtube

What is OSINT? (Open Source Intelligence)
-Intelligence gathered from publicly available data
  -the more relevant the better
-pnetesters use this often
-types:
  -humint (from humans spies)
  -sigint (from signal intercepts)
  -comint (communications intelligince)
  -elint (electronic intelligence)

How attackers get in OT network
-from IT (remote access)
-physical cyber assets
-control systems exposed to the internet
-Exploit database
  -has known exploits for pentesters
